<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-06T20:13:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-06T20:13:00-05:00" n="104" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1236</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-07T10:00:00+08:47"><hi rend="italic">March 7, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 7, 7.54
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>My cipher telegram March 6, 10 p.m. Four Chamber of Commerce members
                                arrested yesterday were released last night without violence and
                                attempted arrest of Soviet was postponed till to-night.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_CJK1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>